From 39eeefb8905eb007f4bc3f958685dd761759cd35 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chris Burr <christopher.burr@cern.ch>
Date: Tue, 3 Mar 2026 11:41:10 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 3/5] fix: Use C++ linker for libRivet convenience library
 aggregation

libRivet_la_SOURCES is empty since the library is assembled purely
from convenience sub-libraries. As documented in the GNU Automake
manual (section 8.3.5, Libtool Convenience Libraries), this causes
automake to default to the C linker, which does not link the C++
standard library. This can lead to crashes when the C++ runtime
symbols are resolved from a different libc++ than the one used by
Rivet's dependencies (e.g. YODA), causing double-frees in std::locale
during YODA::Writer::write.

Apply the standard automake idiom of adding a dummy C++ source via
nodist_EXTRA to force C++ linking.
---
 src/Makefile.am | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/Makefile.am b/src/Makefile.am
index 8c9fc632b..76a1658c1 100644
--- a/src/Makefile.am
+++ b/src/Makefile.am
@@ -2,6 +2,11 @@ SUBDIRS = Core Tools Projections AnalysisTools
 
 lib_LTLIBRARIES = libRivet.la
 
+# Force C++ linking (see GNU Automake manual, section 8.3.5). Without this,
+# automake defaults to the C linker because libRivet_la_SOURCES is empty,
+# which omits the C++ standard library from the link and can cause crashes
+# when multiple libc++ copies are present at runtime.
+nodist_EXTRA_libRivet_la_SOURCES = dummy.cc
 libRivet_la_SOURCES =
 
 libRivet_la_LDFLAGS = -export-dynamic -avoid-version -L$(YODALIBPATH)
